news.title: Jaipur: For residents of two slums, getting land deeds, regularisation of colonies a mirage
news.para: In fact, many residents in these localities have a fear that the administration may one day demolish their houses because the colonies are yet to be regularised.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body drops plan of giving commercial tag to Sarabha Nagar
news.para: ​The latest move has come following severe criticism from residents, who had described the proposal as illegal saying that the area was purely residential.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government gives YEIDA Rs 1,800 crore for five industrial parks
news.para: The Authority, which will contribute an equal amount to facilitate the land acquisition, will repay the state loan in 25 years.

news.title: UID project takes off, 1,000 properties get tag in Ludhiana
news.para: After mapping nearly 1.25 lakh properties, the civic body has installed as many as 1,000 UID number plates so far.

news.title: Nagpur civic body attaches five properties over Rs 28 lakh tax default
news.para: On Friday, Mangalwari zone of NMC led by assistant municipal commissioner Prakash Warade issued seizure warrants against 15 property tax defaulters.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to bring paying guests under regulations
news.para: The BBMP move follows complaints from several resident welfare organisations and citizen groups about how many residential neighbourhoods are slowly being turned into commercial areas with a spurt in PG accommodations.

news.title: Chandigarh: 24 commercial properties likely to face sealing
news.para: “There is a laid down process and procedure to recover the property tax. Following that, we served recovery notices to the defaulters, giving them ample time to deposit the amount,” sources in the civic body said.

news.title: Mussoorie Dehradun development body seals building on Mall Road for flouting norms
news.para: The move came after TOI had reported several anomalies in the sanction of the map of the building and norms and guidelines being flouted during construction.

news.title: Gurugram: Raze unsafe Paradiso towers at earliest, Chintels India told
news.para: The move comes days after Tower D witnessed its second vertical collapse when balconies came crashing down from the fifth floor to the second.

news.title: Delhi HC grants bail to ex-Amrapali Group director in four cases
news.para: ​The homebuyers have alleged that in spite of the payment of the majority of the consideration amount, the projects were either stalled or abandoned or the possession of flats was given in a highly-delayed and incomplete manner.

news.title: Pune civic body extends deadline to fill PT3 form to January 2024
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) received only around 79,000 PT3 forms till the earlier deadline of November 15. Around 2 lakh declarations about self-occupied properties are expected.

news.title: Pune civic body eases side margin rule, redevelopment hope for old wadas
news.para: A notification issued by Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) on Thursday has paved the way for redeveloping old properties in gaothan and peth areas by relaxing the rules for side margins during reconstruction after paying hardship premium charges.

news.title: Book builders if stop-work notice ignored, BMC chief tells squads
news.para: If construction sites fail to follow the norms the BMC issued last month, the squads first issue stop-work notices with the directive to promptly toe the line, but work at some of these sites have continued without so much as a pause.

news.title: Sweden's SBB offers $650 million debt buyback
news.para: Loss-making SBB is at the epicentre of a Swedish property crash, having racked up vast debt by buying public real estate, including social housing, government offices, schools and hospitals.

news.title: Priyanka Chopra sells two Mumbai apartments to director Abhishek Chaubey
news.para: Both the houses on the 9th floor of tower Karan Apartment in Lokhandwala area are cumulatively spread over nearly 2,300 sq ft. Priyanka’s mother Madhu Chopra has executed both the deals on the actor’s behalf.

news.title: Berlin's renters face more misery as housing crisis deepens
news.para: The German capital, where cheap and abundant apartments were a magnet for artists and young professionals as recently as a decade ago, now has a vacancy rate of less than 1%.

news.title: Puravankara looks to hand over 2,500 units in H2 FY24
news.para: "So we are expecting that out of the 15 projects, at least 12 to 13 projects definitely will go to the market by March 2024," said Abhishek Kapoor, executive director & CEO, Puravankara.

news.title: Navi Mumbai metro rail line 1 services for public to begin from Nov 17: CIDCO
news.para: ​In a release, the City and Industrial Development Corporation said services on the 11.10 kilometre route were being thrown open to the public on the direction of Chief Minister Eknath Shinde "without any official programme".

news.title: Signatureglobal (India) to invest Rs 50-60 crore to develop 20 acres land parcels in Gurugram
news.para: Signatureglobal (India) entered into a joint development agreement (JDA) for 16.12 acres land in village Fazilpur, sector 71 while 4.26 acres land parcel is under land collaboration.
